FAR in the windings of a vale
scorn This charmer of the plains
each youth with love , Each maiden with despair
What happy hours of homefelt bliss
What happy hours of homefelt bliss
mischief joyed , To work them harm , with wicked skill
In EDWIN's gentle heart , a war Of differing passions
His heart , that durst not disobey , Yet could not cease to love
In EDWIN's gentle heart , a war Of differing passions
The spreading hawthorn crept , To snatch a glance , to mark the spot Where EMMA walked and wept
homeward as she hopeless wept The churchyard path along
Now homeward as she hopeless wept The churchyard path along
every bush his hovering shade , His groan in every sound
Just then she reached , with trembling step
